MAMELODI Sundowns Percy Tau and Maritzburg United midfield maestro were the big winners at the Absa Premier Soccer League awards ceremony on Monday evening. Tau played a enormmous role as Sundowns clinched their eighth Absa Premiership title, scoring 11 goals and providing 15 assists in the 2017-18 PSL season. The 24-year-old Mpumalanga born player bagged both the PSL Footballer of the Season and the Player’s Player of the Season awards and on top he added the joint goalscorer accolade which he shared with Polokwane City striker Rodney Ramagalela. Tau was not the only winner from the Brazillins as his coach Pitso Mosimane also claimed the Coach of the Season honour, ahead of Fadlu Davids of Maritzburg United and Orlando Pirates mentor Milutin Sredojevic. Maritzburg also had a night to remember as they collected four Awards on the night with Ndlovu bagged the PSL Young Player of the Season and midfielder of the season accolades after his incredible season he had. Lebogang Maboe earned another award the other two awards for the team of choice as he took the Nedbank Cup Most Improved Player of the Tournament and Player of the Tournament. Golden Arrows midfielder, Siphelele Magubane, scooped the Goal of the Season award, his goal voted for by the football public. AWARD WINNERSFootballer of the Season: Percy Tau (Mamelodi Sundowns)Premiership Player’s Player of the Season: Percy TauPremiership Coach of the Season: Pitso Mosimane (Sundowns)Premiership Young Player of the Season: Siphesihle Ndlovu (Maritzburg United)Premiership Goalkeeper of the Season: Itumeleng Khune (Kaizer Chiefs)Premiership Defender of the Season: Siyanda Xulu (Maritzburg United)Premiership Midfielder of the Season: Siphesihle Ndlovu (Maritzburg United)Premiership Goal of the Season: Siphelele Magubane (Golden Arrows)MTN8 Last Man Standing: Ronwen Williams (SuperSport United)Telkom Knockout Player of the Tournament: Amr Gamal (Bidvest Wits)Nedbank Cup Player of the Tournament: Lebogang Maboe (Maritzburg United)Nedbank Cup Most Promising Player: Lebogang Maboe (Maritzburg United)Multichoice Diski Challenge: Siboniso Conco (Golden Arrows)Multichoice Diski Shield: Itumeleng Shopane (Kaizer Chiefs)